NNAAMMEE
       simple_shell - A simple UNIX command interpreter


SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ssiimmppllee__sshheellll [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s]

       #include "StarHeader.h"


DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       ssiimmppllee__sshheellll  is  a simple UNIX command interpreter that mimics the be-
       havior of the standard UNIX shell. It reads  commands  from  the  user,
       parses  them,  and  executes them as if they were entered in a standard
       shell.

       The simple_shell supports the execution of built-in commands as well as
       external commands found in the system's PATH. It also handles basic er-
       ror reporting, argument parsing, and process management.


OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       ssiimmppllee__sshheellll does not have any command-line options. It  runs  interac-
       tively  by default, waiting for user input in a loop until the user ex-
       its the shell.


CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       The following commands are built into ssiimmppllee__sshheellll::


       ccdd     Change the current directory.  Usage: _c_d _[_d_i_r_e_c_t_o_r_y_]


       ccdd ....  Move up one level in the directory tree.  _c_d _._.


       ccdd //   Change the current working directory to the root directory.   _c_d
              _/


       ccdd ~~   Return to your personal directory.  _c_d _~


       eexxiitt   Exit the shell.  Usage: _e_x_i_t _[_s_t_a_t_u_s_]


       hheellpp   Display a help message with a list of built-in commands.


       eecchhoo   Displays a line of text or a variable.  _e_c_h_o _[_s_t_r_i_n_g_]


       eennvv    Display the current environment variables.  _e_n_v


UUSSAAGGEE
       When ssiimmppllee__sshheellll is run, it displays a prompt where the user can enter
       commands. The shell will then execute the command  and  return  to  the
       prompt.

       For example:


EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
       $  simple_shell  simple_shell>  ls  -l  total 64 -rwxrwxr-x 1 user user
       16384 Aug 12 12:34 hsh -rw-rw-r-- 1 user user  1048 Aug 12 12:30 main.c
       simple_shell> echo "Hello, World!"  Hello, World!  simple_shell> exit $


       RRuunnnniinngg aa ssiimmppllee ccoommmmaanndd
              Run the `ls` command to list directory contents:
              $ simple_shell
              simple_shell> ls -la


EEXXIITT SSTTAATTUUSS
       ssiimmppllee__sshheellll exits with the status of the last command executed. If the
       eexxiitt command is used, the shell will exit with the status specified  by
       the user.


FFIILLEESS
       ssiimmppllee__sshheellll  does  not use any external configuration files. All func-
       tionality is implemented within the binary.


